Class ProjectCustomException

java.lang.Object
java.lang.Throwable
java.lang.Exception
functional.genericKeywords.ProjectCustomException
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class ProjectCustomException extends Exception
Custom exception class for project-specific exceptions in a test-driven development framework. This exception is used to handle and report errors specific to the project's testing scenarios.

    • ProjectCustomException

      public ProjectCustomException(String failedClassName, String failedMethodName, Exception exceptionDetails, String message)
      Constructs a new ProjectCustomException with detailed information about the failure. It logs the failed scenario, closes the browser, and captures the exception details and a custom message.
      Parameters:
      failedClassName - The name of the class where the failure occurred.
      failedMethodName - The name of the method where the failure occurred.
      exceptionDetails - The exception details of the failure.
      message - The custom message for the exception.
